nition of requirements and capabilities of system baselines through the end-of-life of each system. In addition, the CM will provide CM planning, defining provisions for configuration identification, change control, configuration status accounting, and configuration audits. The CM will regulate the change process so that only approved and validated changes are incorporated. WORKING ENVIRONMENT: Office working location. The CM will provide remote support and/or travel to customer sites as required. PHYSICAL ACTIVITIES: Will be required to sit for extended periods of time. Qualifications MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS: Education/Certifications: One year related experience may be substituted for one year of education, if degree is required. Currently hold an adjudicated Secret Clearance and be able to maintain Professional certification that meets or exceeds DoD 8570.01 IAT 2 (CompTIA Security +, equal or greater) Information Technology Information Library (ITIL) Intermediate Release, Control, and validation (RCV) Must be willing/able to work OCONUS for minimum of one year Provide technical leadership and cross-training to peers in areas of expertise Act as a resource to team members, participates in team and professional meetings Coaches and provides input as to the needs of Infrastructure staff; Provide 3rd line technical support as needed Five years of experience as a configuration manager in programs and contracts of similar scope, type, and complexity 5 years\u2019 experience using and administering CM tools to store, track, and manage configuration items Effective communications throughout all levels of operational command Experience supporting Command Post of the Future concepts and configurations Ability to document system process and architecture BA/BS +3 yrs recent specialized or AA/AS +7 yrs recent specialized or a major cert + 7 yrs recent specialized or 11 years of recent specialized Nice to Have Qualifications: ITIL v3 Foundation Certification Experience supporti